# Stock Verdict (KabuCheck) — Cline Project Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 16, TypeScript strict, TailwindCSS 4, shadcn/ui (Radix + CVA)
- Recharts for visualizations, TradingView Lightweight Charts for price charts
- yahoo-finance2 for market data, Claude API (Anthropic) for AI narrative
- Supabase + Drizzle ORM for database, Upstash Redis for caching
- Zustand for client UI state, TanStack Query for server state + caching
- next-intl for i18n (EN / JA / PT), Zod for runtime validation
- Vitest + React Testing Library + happy-dom for tests

## Architecture principles

### Server vs Client split
- Move ALL data fetching, API calls, and heavy computation to Next.js Server Components or Route Handlers
- Client Components (`'use client'`) only for: interactivity, browser APIs, event handlers, animations
- Never fetch from Yahoo Finance / Claude / FRED directly in a Client Component
- Use React Server Components (RSC) by default — add `'use client'` only when required
- Pass data down as props from Server Components to Client Components

### File size & structure
- No file should exceed ~150 lines. Split into smaller modules if it grows beyond that.
- One component per file. One hook per file. One service function per file where possible.
- Components go in `src/components/[feature]/ComponentName.tsx`
- Custom hooks go in `src/hooks/use[Name].ts`
- Server-side services go in `src/lib/services/[name]Service.ts`
- API route handlers go in `src/app/api/[route]/route.ts`
- Types go in `src/types/index.ts` or `src/types/[domain].ts`
- Zod schemas go in `src/validators/[domain].ts`

### Custom hooks & state
- Extract any logic > 10 lines from a component into a custom hook
- Use Zustand stores for: language preference, theme, UI filter state, watchlist UI state
- Use TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) for all server state — never `useEffect` + `fetch`
- Keep Zustand stores small and focused — one store per domain (langStore, themeStore, watchlistStore)

### Code style
- TypeScript strict mode — no implicit `any`. Use `unknown` + type narrowing instead.
- If `any` is truly unavoidable, add `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` with a comment explaining why
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use `const` arrow functions for components: `export const MyComponent = () => {}`
- Destructure props at the function signature
- Use early returns to avoid deep nesting

## TDD — Test Driven Development
- Write tests BEFORE or alongside implementation, never after as an afterthought
- Every utility function in `src/lib/` must have a corresponding test in `src/lib/__tests__/`
- Every custom hook must have a test using `renderHook` from React Testing Library
- Every API route handler must have an integration test
- Run `npm run test:run` after every change to verify nothing broke
- Test file naming: `[name].test.ts` or `[name].test.tsx`
- After fixing a bug, always run the full test suite — not just a reproduction script

## After every TypeScript change
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` to verify no type errors before considering the task done

## Documentation
- When adding or changing a feature, update `docs/docs_APP_FEATURES.md` to reflect the change
- When a planned feature moves from "planned" to "in progress" or "done", update the Feature Matrix table

## MCP & tooling
- If a new MCP server would meaningfully help a task (e.g. Playwright for UI verification, GitHub for issue tracking), suggest it to the user before proceeding
- Playwright MCP is available — use it to visually verify UI changes by screenshotting the running app

## Refactoring rules
- When touching a file, refactor it to meet these standards if it doesn't already
- Break up any component > 150 lines into sub-components
- If a component does data fetching AND rendering, split: one Server Component for fetching, one Client Component for rendering
- Remove dead code, unused imports, and commented-out blocks on sight